  "local_port": 57766,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are the various Incarnations of Lord Vishnu and what is going to be the last Incarnation of Lord Vishnu?",
  "response": "Lord Vishnu, one of the principal deities in Hinduism, is known for taking various incarnations, or \"avatars,\" to restore cosmic order and protect the world from evil forces. These incarnations are typically categorized into 10 main avatars known as \"Dashavatara.\" Here is a list of the 10 main incarnations of Lord Vishnu along with a brief description of each:\n\n1. **Matsya (The Fish)**\n   - Matsya avatar is associated with the story of the great flood. Vishnu took the form of a fish to save the first man, Manu, and the seven sages by guiding them to safety.\n\n2. **Kurma (The Tortoise)**\n   - In this avatar, Vishnu took the form of a tortoise to support the mountain Mandara during the churning of the ocean (Samudra Manthan), which was done to obtain the nectar of immortality.\n\n3. **Varaha (The Boar)**\n   - Vishnu assumed the form of a boar to rescue the earth goddess, Bhudevi, from the demon Hiranyaksha who had dragged her to the bottom of the cosmic ocean.\n\n4. **Narasimha (The Man-Lion)**\n   - To kill the demon king Hiranyakashipu, who could not be killed by man or animal, day or night, indoors or outdoors, Vishnu took the form of a half-man, half-lion creature and killed him at twilight on the threshold of a courtyard.\n\n5. **Vamana (The Dwarf)**\n   - As a dwarf Brahmin, Vishnu appeared before the demon king Bali and asked for three paces of land. Vamana then grew to an immense size and reclaimed the heavens and earth with two steps, leaving Bali with the netherworld.\n\n6. **Parashurama (The Warrior with an Axe)**\n   - Parashurama was born to rid the earth of corrupt and oppressive Kshatriya rulers. He is said to have traversed the earth 21 times to eradicate these tyrants.\n\n7. **Rama (The Prince of Ayodhya)**\n   - Rama is one of the most celebrated avatars, known for his role in the epic Ramayana. He is considered the embodiment of dharma (righteousness) and is revered for rescuing his wife Sita from the demon king Ravana.\n\n8. **Krishna (The Divine Statesman)**\n   - Krishna, another widely worshipped avatar, played a crucial role in the epic Mahabharata. He delivered the Bhagavad Gita and is revered for his wisdom, charm, and divine playfulness.\n\n9. **Buddha (The Enlightened One)**\n   - In some traditions, Vishnu incarnated as Buddha to guide humanity away from excessive ritualism and towards a more spiritual and ethical path.\n\n10. **Kalki (The Destroyer of Filth)**\n    - Kalki is believed to be the final avatar of Vishnu, who will appear at the end of the Kali Yuga, the current age of darkness and decay. He will come to end the current cycle of time and restore righteousness.\n\nThe last incarnation of Lord Vishnu, as per Hindu scriptures, is expected to be **Kalki**. Kalki is prophesied to appear riding a white horse, wielding a sword, and leading an army to eradicate evil and usher in a new era of truth and purity known as the Satya Yuga. This incarnation is anticipated to bring about the end of the Kali Yuga and mark the beginning of a new cycle of creation.",
  "response_tokens": [
